ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Holloman Lessee, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
HOLLOMAN LESSEE, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Holloman Lessee, LLC ("Holloman") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Holloman generating facility ("Holloman Facility").
The Holloman Facility is a solar generating facility located in Aulander, North Carolina. The Holloman Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Holloman's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Holloman Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Holloman's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Holloman shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $1,790,395.81. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $149,199.65.
